review_blob: I used to love this stuff when I was younger, and before I developed a taste for GOOD beer. Its another one of Molsons watered down dirty sock tasting brews. A bit cheaper then your regular Molson beers, but with all the same  taste youd expect from them. If you want a cheaper dry with a slightly more better taste then most of their mass produced swill, then pick up a case of this.
A light feeling dark ale that has a nice chocolate caramel taste reminiscent of  English ales like Newcastle Brown. Definitely less carbonation than my liking, but still a nice brew.

A thicker floral tasting beer which is definitely an acquired taste. Cloudy and pours with a fantastic head. Has an aroma of strong hops and an overall floral taste as mentioned before. A great winter beer that at 9% will keep you warm on those cold nights. So far my favorite of the Unibroue brews Ive tasted.

One of my favorite summer beers. Has an almost medium body to it, with a distinct malt taste and tiny hints of pepper or herbs. Not overly carbonated. Great on hot summer day with a lemon or lime in it.
Never been a huge fan of  the Coffee Porters, but this one might convert me to the darkside.  Its not too sweet or too strong of a coffee flavor, and its a nice refreshing drink for any time of year.
